      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Distinct weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on northeast, north and northwest facing slopes. This applies especially above approximately 1900 m. <br/> <br/> Outgoing longwave radiation during the night was good over a wide area. Towards its surface, the snowpack consists of faceted crystals, especially in areas where the snow cover is rather shallow on shady slopes. <br/> <br/> Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be quite good at times. The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust. There is a danger of falling on the hard crust. The weather conditions as the day progresses will give rise to softening of the snowpack in particular on very steep sunny slopes. <br/> <br/> Backcountry tours should be started early and concluded timely."
      },
      "source": {
        "provider": {
          "name": "LWD K\u00e4rnten",
          "website": "https://lawinenwarndienst.ktn.gv.at/?lang=en"
        }
      },
